The error in Step 4 is that the Identity Theorem applies to an analytic function on a connected open subset of \(\mathbb{C}\), but \(|x^k|\) is not analytic on any open interval containing both positive and negative real parts. Hence it cannot be used to deduce uniqueness over \(\mathbb{C}\).

Step 5 (Corrected): There is no entire function agreeing with \(|x^k|\) for all \(x \in \mathbb{C}\), since \(|x^k|\) is not analytic except possibly at isolated points (namely \(x=0\)). Therefore, \(\mathbb{F}\) is empty.

